          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":55,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Long run at easy effort, 5:22–5:56/km. Keep it conversational and relaxed. 20 km target. Great opportunity to practice fueling every 45 min.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Prioritize sleep and nutrition to support recovery from yesterday's long run.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy recovery run, 8 km at 5:39–5:56/km. Legs may feel heavy — that's normal. Keep effort genuinely easy.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"Tempo session: 2 km warm-up, 8 km at 4:28/km threshold pace, 2 km cool-down (12 km total). Focus on smooth, controlled effort — comfortably hard.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 6 km at 5:39–5:56/km. Active recovery between quality sessions. No pressure on pace.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Interval\",\"notes\":\"Interval session: 2 km warm-up, 5×1 km at 4:11/km with 400 m jog recovery, 1.6 km cool-down (10 km total). Controlled and sharp — not an all-out sprint.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 9 km at 5:22–5:56/km. Flush out the legs from Friday's intervals. Relaxed effort throughout.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to your maintenance plan, Maria. This first week mirrors the structure you've been executing well — a long run, one tempo, one interval session, and easy volume to fill the week. Total target is 55 km, consistent with your current base. The goal here is to preserve your VDOT 46.7 fitness without adding stress. You're in a strong place after Chicago and Boston, and this plan respects that. Keep your easy days genuinely easy — that's the most common mistake at your level, and protecting your recovered Achilles starts with honest effort management on recovery days.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
